{"parse":{"title":"MakeBelieve Arts","pageid":29636318,"revid":856050286,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>MakeBelieve Arts</b> is a <a href=\"/wiki/Theatre_in_education\" title=\"Theatre in education\">theatre in education</a> company, based in <a href=\"/wiki/Corsham,_Wiltshire\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Corsham, Wiltshire\">Corsham, Wiltshire</a> and constituted as a <a href=\"/wiki/Social_enterprise\" title=\"Social enterprise\">social enterprise</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> The company works with children aged 2\u201311 and their teachers, families and community. It uses theatre techniques within education to deliver creative, interactive workshops that seek to reflect, support and enhance the curriculum and to encourage <a href=\"/wiki/Lifelong_learning\" title=\"Lifelong learning\">lifelong learning</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-business.timesonline.co.uk_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-business.timesonline.co.uk-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> MakeBelieve Arts' approach is underpinned by current educational philosophy.<sup id=\"cite_ref-business.timesonline.co.uk_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-business.timesonline.co.uk-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>MakeBelieve Arts pioneered the Helicopter Stories approach in the UK. This approach is based on the work of <a href=\"/wiki/Vivian_Gussin_Paley\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Vivian Gussin Paley\">Vivian Gussin Paley</a> who is patron to MakeBelieve Arts. In its simplest form Helicopter Stories involves practitioners in scribing stories dictated by children in the Early Years. These stories are then acted out around a taped out stage. In 2016 Trisha Lee published a guide on the approach. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.routledge.com/Princesses-Dragons-and-Helicopter-Stories-Storytelling-and-story-acting/Lee/p/book/9781138797659\">Princesses, Dragons and Helicopter Stories</a> \n</p><p>Helicopter Stories is a registered trademark of MakeBelieve Arts.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Educational_philosophy\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Educational philosophy</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Social_enterprise\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Social enterprise</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=MakeBelieve_Arts&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: History\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>MakeBelieve Arts was founded by Trisha Lee in 2002. The programmes in schools and the community are delivered by Trisha Lee as Artistic Director and Isla Hill as Education Director, alongside a pool of creative associates and consultants, including the author <a href=\"/wiki/David_Baird_(author)\" title=\"David Baird (author)\">David Baird</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Educational_philosophy\">Educational philosophy</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=MakeBelieve_Arts&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Educational philosophy\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>MakeBelieve Arts is guided by thinking such as that of the British educationalist Sir <a href=\"/wiki/Ken_Robinson_(British_author)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ken Robinson (British author)\">Ken Robinson</a>, who has written that '...creativity is as important to education as literacy, and we should treat it with the same status.'<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> The company has embedded this philosophy into all its work.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>The group considers that a creative approach to education allows children and young people to develop into enterprising adults with more job prospects in the future.<sup id=\"cite_ref-business.timesonline.co.uk_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-business.timesonline.co.uk-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Trisha Lee stated in <i>The Times</i> that: \n</p>\n<blockquote><p>We aim to give the children life-long skills. The capacity to analyse, discuss and communicate. It is recognised that creativity is really important for employers in the 21st century. Once they have acquired the skills to ask questions and think outside of the box then they can do anything.<sup id=\"cite_ref-business.timesonline.co.uk_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-business.timesonline.co.uk-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Social_enterprise\">Social enterprise</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=MakeBelieve_Arts&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Social enterprise\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>MakeBelieve Arts is a <a href=\"/wiki/Social_enterprise\" title=\"Social enterprise\">social enterprise</a>;<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> it is not core funded and derives funds from a variety of sources. Any profits are reinvested into the company.<sup id=\"cite_ref-socialenterpriseambassadors.org.uk_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-socialenterpriseambassadors.org.uk-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Trisha Lee (founder and Artistic Director) was a Cabinet-appointed Social Enterprise Ambassador from mid-2007 to mid-2010.<sup id=\"cite_ref-socialenterpriseambassadors.org.uk_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-socialenterpriseambassadors.org.uk-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>  With 28 other leading social entrepreneurs in the country, Trisha Lee sought to raise awareness about social enterprise and encourage other arts organisations to think creatively and become social enterprises.<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=MakeBelieve_Arts&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist columns references-column-width\" style=\"-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em; list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Barbara Eifler (ed), \"Rehearsal Rooms: A place to call home\", <i>The Stage</i>, London, pp. 28-29, 7 October 2010</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-business.timesonline.co.uk-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-business.timesonline.co.uk_2-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-business.timesonline.co.uk_2-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-business.timesonline.co.uk_2-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-business.timesonline.co.uk_2-3\"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://business.timesonline.co.uk/tol/business/related_reports/social_entrepreneurs/article6389902.ece\">The Times Online</a>, 2009</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.goodreads.com/author/quotes/43940.Ken_Robinson\">Good Reads</a>, 2010</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.lonsas.org.uk/arts_directory_detail.aspx?OrganisationID=371\">LONSAS</a>, 2010</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.socialenterprise.org.uk/pages/about-social-enterprise.html\">Social Enterprise Coalition</a>, 2010</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-socialenterpriseambassadors.org.uk-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-socialenterpriseambassadors.org.uk_6-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-socialenterpriseambassadors.org.uk_6-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://socialenterpriseambassadors.org.uk/ambassador/trisha-lee\">\"Trisha Lee\"</a>, Social Enterprise Ambassadors, 2010</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://socialenterpriseambassadors.org.uk/about-us\">Social Enterprise Ambassadors</a>, 2010</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=MakeBelieve_Arts&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.makebelievearts.co.uk/about-us/\">MakeBelieve Arts</a></li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw2194\nCached time: 20180914092353\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.036 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.048 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 199/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 754/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 97/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 3776/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 0/400\nLua time usage: 0.003/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 525 KB/50 MB\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   25.343      1 Template:Reflist\n100.00%   25.343      1 -total\n  8.73%    2.212      1 Template:Main_other\n  5.45%    1.382      1 Template:Column-width\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key enwiki:pcache:idhash:29636318-0!canonical and timestamp 20180914092353 and revision id 856050286\n -->\n</div>"},"langlinks":[],"categories":[{"sortkey":"","*":"Theatre_in_education"}],"links":[{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Corsham, Wiltshire"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"David Baird (author)"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Ken Robinson (British author)"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Lifelong learning"},{"ns":0